## Performance Best Practices

### Replication and Durability (CRITICAL)

**Set replication factor to 3 or higher at topic creation time.**

```
⚠️ CRITICAL: Setting replication factor AFTER creation requires expensive 
   partition reassignment that copies data over the network.
```

**Best Practice**: Get this right initially.

```bash
# ✅ GOOD: Set replication at creation
kafka-topics.sh --create --topic my-topic \
  --partitions 12 \
  --replication-factor 3

# ❌ BAD: Changing later requires network-intensive reassignment
kafka-topics.sh --alter --topic my-topic \
  --replication-factor 3  # Expensive operation!
```

**Source**: [Kafka Best Practices](https://karafka.io/docs/Kafka-Best-Practices/)

### Performance Optimization

1. **Use columnar formats**: Avro, Parquet for better compression
2. **Monitor lag**: Consumer lag indicates performance issues
3. **Tune fetch settings**: `fetch.min.bytes`, `fetch.max.wait.ms`
4. **Use latest client versions**: Performance improvements in newer versions

