## Anti-Patterns

### ❌ Anti-Pattern 1: Prime Number Partitions

```
❌ BAD: 3, 7, 11 partitions (hard to distribute evenly)
✅ GOOD: 6, 12, 24, 60 partitions (many divisors)
```

### ❌ Anti-Pattern 2: Too Many Partitions Per Broker

```
❌ BAD: 5,000+ partitions per broker (degraded performance)
✅ GOOD: Stay under 4,000 partitions per broker
```

### ❌ Anti-Pattern 3: Changing Partition Count Later

```
❌ BAD: Add partitions after creation (breaks key-based ordering)
✅ GOOD: Calculate partition needs upfront
```

### ❌ Anti-Pattern 4: Low Replication Factor

```
❌ BAD: replication-factor=1 (data loss on broker failure)
✅ GOOD: replication-factor=3+ (durability)
```

### ❌ Anti-Pattern 5: Using ZooKeeper for New Deployments

```
❌ BAD: ZooKeeper (removed in Kafka 4.0)
✅ GOOD: KRaft mode (supports 2M partitions, faster failovers)
```

